snippet: The problems with HealthCare.gov have lit a fire under the West Wing staff, but some Democrats close to the White House think that the Obama administration is not sufficiently panicked.
abstract: Problems with HealthCare.gov have sent West Wing staff scrambling to fix it, but some Democrats think that the Obama administration is not sufficiently panicked; there is anxiety that if the health care problems are not righted, they could imperil the rest of Obama’s presidency, especially as criticism grows that the president misled consumers about the plan.
lead_paragraph: The problems with HealthCare.gov have lit a fire under the West Wing staff, but some Democrats close to the White House think that the Obama administration is not sufficiently panicked.

headline.main: A White House in Crisis Mode, but Some Allies Prod for More Action
